oth genetics and the sciences of complexity since the book's original publication.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEvolution (Biology). 0aMorphology. 0aSelf-organizing systems. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology.2bisacsh  aAcanthostega (fossil tetrapod).  aBarlow, Kenneth.  aBeloussov, Boris.  aBeloussov-Zhabotinsky reaction.  aCoriolis force.  aDarwin, Charles.  aDasycladales (algae).  aGaia hypothesis.  aKant, Immanuel.  aLamarckian inheritance.  aalternate phyllotaxis.  aattractors.  aautopoesis.  abifurcations.  acausation.  acellular automata.  adolphins.  aentropy.  aexcitable media.  aflower primordia.  agenocentric biology.  ahistorical explanations.  ahomunculus theory.  ainfarcts.  ainvariant sets.  ainverse problem.  alimb buds.  ameristems.  amonocotyledons.  amoving boundary problems.  anatural history.  aneurulation.  aorganisms.  aparastichies.  aphyllotaxy.  aquantum mechanics.  asociobiology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691217802zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691217802423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691217802.jpg  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK